'''Benedict of Soracte''' ('''Benedict of St. Andrew''') was a tenth-century [[Italy|Italian]] [[chronicler]], a monk at the monastery on [[Soracte|Mount Soracte]]. The ''[[Catholic Encyclopedia]]'' article on ''Ecclesiastical Annals'' dates his chronicle to 968, but notes that it "unfortunately, is filled with legends".<ref>[http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/01531b.htm Ecclesiastical Annals; Annals in Italy]</ref>
