'''Suzanne Aspden''' is professor of music at [[Jesus College, Oxford|Jesus College]], [[University of Oxford]]. She was formerly a research fellow at [[Robinson College, Cambridge|Robinson College]], University of Cambridge from 1999 to 2002 and a lecturer in music at the [[University of Southampton]] from 2002 to 2005. In 2002-3 she was the first John Marshall and Marie Louise Osborn Fellow at the [[Beinecke Library]], Yale University.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jesus.ox.ac.uk/people/professor-suzanne-aspden|title=Professor Suzanne Aspden - Jesus College, University of Oxford|website=Jesus.ox.ac.uk|accessdate=19 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.music.ox.ac.uk/about/people/academic-staff/university-lecturers-and-college-fellows/suzanne-apsden/|title=Suzanne Aspden - Oxford University Faculty of Music|website=Music.ox.ac.uk|accessdate=19 December 2017}}</ref>
==Selected publications== * ''The Rival Sirens: Performance and Identity on Handel’s Operatic Stage''. [[Cambridge University Press]], [[Cambridge]], 2013.
